# ARTS Configuration Files

## Configuration File Structure
ARTS configuration files use INI format with `[ARTS]` section header.

## Essential Configuration Options

### Threading Configuration
```ini
threads=16          # Number of worker threads
tMT=0              # Temporal multi-threading (0=disabled, max=64)
```

### GPU Support (Future)
```ini
scheduler=3         # GPU scheduler type
gpu=8              # Number of GPUs
gpuRouteTableSize=12 # GPU route table size
```

### Network Configuration
```ini
outgoing=1         # Outgoing network threads
incoming=1         # Incoming network threads
ports=1           # Network ports
```

### Launcher Configuration
```ini
launcher=ssh       # Launch method (ssh, slurm, lsf)
masterNode=localhost # Master node for SSH launcher
nodeCount=1        # Number of nodes
nodes=localhost    # Which nodes to run on
```

### Performance Monitoring
```ini
counterFolder=./counters/  # Performance counter directory
counterStartPoint=1        # Counter start point
printNodeStats=1          # Print node statistics
```

### Memory and Performance
```ini
workerInitDequeSize=2048  # Initial deque size
routeTableSize=16         # Routing table size
pinThreads=1             # Hardware pinning
```

## Example Configuration
See examples in test directories like [test/tasksimple/arts.cfg](mdc:test/tasksimple/arts.cfg):
```ini
[ARTS]
threads=16
tMT=0
outgoing=1
incoming=1
ports=1
launcher=ssh
masterNode=localhost
nodeCount=1
counterFolder=./counters/
counterStartPoint=1
```

## Configuration Locations
- Test directories: `test/*/arts.cfg`
- Example directories: `examples/*/arts.cfg`
- Each executable needs its own configuration file
